  @{"°"} @{"  More Information  "} @{"°°"} @{"°"}


   To have your name  included in the main @{" MAXs Door Coders " link start} listing, you
   must be (or was) a coder (programmer)  who has coded at  least three or
   more executable doors or utils  for the MAXs BBS 1.54 and/or  MAXs PRO.
   These doors in  concern must have been  released to the MAXs Public and
   should be located on Aminet or a MAXs Support list or on  GREMLiNS BBS!
   Also, these doors would run via MAXs BBS itself or be an external util.

   If you are not a MAXs Door Coder, and don't  fall into the above guide-
   lines, but you are  a contributor to  MAXs since you have created a few
   MAXs  support  files/packages,  then you may be  included in  the other
   listing, @{" Coders & Origins " link list}. Your files must also have been released to
   the MAXs Public, and somewhere online. To be in  the "Coders & Origins"
   listing, advice  me of your full name and what support  files you have
   created, and/or send these files to me.

   If you are applicable to be in the MAXs Door Coders list, then you must
   complete the following application form in full, brief and to the point
   and simply return it to myself, via email or other means.  See my entry
   for an @{" example " link gm} of a completed application form, and related info. You
   may only use your real name, and be truthful in completing this info.

   My decision is final in regards to which list you fall in, okay! :)

   @{" Application Form " link form} is also included in this archive!

   Upon completing  Application Form, email to address below.  If need
   be, you may contact me via the following details:

   Email .......: gmartin@technet2000.com.au
   Snail Mail ..: PO BOX 1028, Beenleigh, Queensland 4207, Australia
   BBS .........: GREMLiNS BBS +61-7-3807-6884 (24 Hours Weekends Only)
   Fluffy Net ..: 888:601/0.0 (public msg), Australian Regional HQ

   Regards,
