  -----------------
   @{b}About the Coder@{ub}
  =================

  Origin: ............... Australia     Alias: .................... Marty
  Home: ...... Brisbane, Queensland     Date of Birth: ........ 14-Dec-73

  Job: .... Work for a Credit Union     Food: ........... Junk food/Pizza
  Sport: ...... Cricket/Touch Footy     Movie: ................... Aliens
  TV: . X-Files/Simpsons/South Park     Music: ............... Most types
  Game: ................. PSX games     PC: .............. Amiga 2000/030
  Event: .......... Going to movies     Pastime: ....... Sex, work & life

  ----------------
   @{b}Coders History@{ub}
  ================

  It all started when my mate gave me a box, a slow 2400 modem in 1994.
  I plugged it into my computer and this was my first experience with
  the modem and BBS world. I soon logged onto a few BBS's, and got to
  know how it all worked. One SysOp showed me his BBS, and explained it
  all to me in more detail. I became involved, and wanted my own BBS.

  Late 1994 or so, I started my own small BBS using MAXs BBS 1.54 and
  this was my first encounter with MAXs. I then moved around and the BBS
  went with me. I then thought about programming and another SysOp got
  me started and helped me out. Before I knew it, I was programming a
  heap of doors for the great MAXs BBS, first door evolving in 1995 and
  many more doors created, right up till now. I still program today!?

  ------------------
