   @{b}Other Information@{ub}
  ===================


  o My 1st MAXs door was "CallBBS.lha" and the 2nd was "UserMsg.lha".

  o I'm no expert programmer and only know BASIC, my knowledge is not that
    great. I only learn what I need to know to program for MAXs doors only
    and this is just as a part-time hobby for me, with running a BBS! Yes,
    I could become a great programmer if I wanted too,  but no thanks, I'm
    happy with what I know and can create for the great MAXs BBS! :-) Hey,
    I still don't even understand half the code I write! Eeek, hehe. And I
    still manage to write a shitload of MAXs doors, and decent at that!?

  o I started my BBS, which was 1stly named as Gremlin BBS.  This BBS name
    was the 1st I came up with, it stuck... but later changed to Gremlins.
    I started  my 24 Hr BBS  in Townsville, QLD,  then moved to Melbourne,
    VIC and went online there,  then moved back to Townsville (Mar-95) and
    again online (but only part-time).  Moved back to Melbourne (Sep-95) &
    didn't go back online till 25th April 96,  which is the BBS's birthday
    even though it's not the true BBS's birthday, as GREMLiNS BBS had been
    online longer since that date,  it was considered a turning point, and
    the true beginning of the BBS,  as I saw it. The BBS went to two lines
    in mid-97 and was doing extremely well.  I took on Fluffy Net and took
    on MAXsPRO during these days online in Melbourne.  Then sadly, I moved
    again in Oct-97 but  for a good reason (..Zeffy). I moved to Brisbane,
    QLD and the BBS did not go back online till Mar-98, and here I am now!

  o I've had a total 4 Co-SysOps, help run the BBS.  I've had more than 30
    users donate to the BBS (over $300 in total).  Have had 2 BBS losses &
    3 times have started my BBS from scratch (re-worked).  I've gone thru'
    and lost a keyboard, monitor and 2 HD's during the BBS years.  Am onto
    my 3rd modem.  Have had a total of 7 lines installed for the BBS since
    all my moves (..holy shit!),  that's about $1200 I've spent and that's
    not  including the 100's of  dollars in phone calls (..ouch)!  I think
    I am one of the most dedicated  BBS SysOps on Earth, and all for MAXs!
    And I certainly have the right to boast about that! :) It's addictive.

  o I've assisted many new SysOps & have helped set up  heaps of new BBS's
    in Australia, using MAXs BBS (..of course), with what I know.

  o I love to hear from MAXs SysOps across the world, and recieve and send
    emails all the time, and love to help those who ask for it, for MAXs..

  Regards,
